                <td valign="top" class="row1"> <span class="smalltext"><b></b></span>
                  <p><span class="largetext">Speaking as one who has left the guild . . . let me just go one by one through the points <img src="images/smiles/icon_cool.gif" alt="icon_cool.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: darkblue">Rule 1: Enjoy Every Day You Play. 
<br />
If you aren't enjoying the game every day you play, change how you play. </span>
<br />
I wasn't enjoying the game every day, so I changed how I played.
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: darkblue">Rule 2: The Grass Is Not Greener. 
<br />
Envy and greed are the two most destructive emotions in Everquest. They lead to the only real destruction that can happen in this game, the destruction of friendships. </span>
<br />
I didn't leave the guild due to envy and greed.  I left it to further pursue other friendships that had begun to develop considering the majority of my friends in KoA had either already left or had stopped playing as much or at all.
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: darkblue">Rule 3: Gear, Experience, Levels, and AAs, aren't real. Friendships are. 
<br />
The only thing you take away from your time in Everquest are experiences and friendships.</span>
<br />
Everyone I was friends with in KoA is still on my friends list...some still talk to me and others seem to hate me for going.  Now how is that bad friendship on my part?
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: darkblue">Rule 4: Items, Levels, Characters, and worlds will fall apart in ten years. What will you walk away with?</span>
<br />
I'll walk away with friendships with people that liked me for me and not because I was in their guild...to me thats most important.
<br />

<br />
I'll actually leave out Rule 5 because I dont think that was being referred to anyway.  
<br />

<br />
But there were many reasons I left KoA and none of them were because I wanted to hurt anyone or lose friendships I had "thought" I had made.  I had hoped that all the people I had been friends with in KoA would remain my friend once I was gone.  It's sad that I was mistaken.  But maybe all the people that are still in KoA that are so pissed at those who left should make sure they read Suvim's post because friendships are important whether that person be in your guild or not.  Saying that the people who have left and have tried so hard to remain in touch with their "friends" from the guild need to read this is just wrong considering its the people left in the guild that have decided to break ties so to speak.  But I guess some people interpret things differently.  Just my opinion... <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
    ~Tibi~
<br />
65 Shammy</span><span class="smalltext"></span></p>
