                <td valign="top" class="row1"> <span class="smalltext"><b></b></span>
                  <p><span class="largetext">I don't think they took the original thread as directed towards them but another comment that was made. I can see why Tibi responded the way she did. Once again Cho and Tibi and others must defend themselves on why they decided to leave KoA. I'm not trying to keep this thread going in a way to be negative because that's not the intention of the thread, but I'm tired of seeing people being made to feel bad because they want to be happy in this game. Like many people have said..that is the whole point of this game. And if people left to be "uber"  ..so what..if that's what they want from the game so be it. When they leave and don't remain your friends..then someone is not doing their end of the friendship. Takes both sides to contribute to a friendship..not just one. I can honestly say that the majority of the people that have left KoA I am still friends with unless they have left the game for real "uber" things =) Anyways..I'm done..sorry if I might seem so negative on such a positive thread..but I had to say it.
